Direct Known Subclasses:
OrderedCountingSet
public class CountingSet
extends Set

A class for storing elements without duplicates or a specified order (as in the mathematical set concept). Unlike the parent class Set, this class counts the number of times each element has been added to the list. The count for an element is increased when the element is added and decreased when the element is removed.

Thread Safety:
Static methods are thread-safe. Instance methods are not guaranteed to be thread-safe.

Author:
Tobias Persson
